#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.29:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.29:0.2"
msgid "3. Udāyivagga"
msgstr "3. With Udāyī"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.29:0.3"
msgid "29. Ekadhammasutta"
msgstr "29. One Thing"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.29:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekadhammampi samanupassāmi, yo evaṃ bhāvito "
"bahulīkato saṃyojanīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya saṃvattati, yathayidaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I do not see a single thing that, when it is developed and "
"cultivated like this, leads to giving up the things that are prone to being "
"fettered like the seven awakening factors."

msgctxt "sn46.29:1.2"
msgid "Katame satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "sn46.29:1.3"
msgid "Satisambojjhaṅgo … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, "
"rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.29:1.4"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā kathaṃ bahulīkatā "
"saṃyojanīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya saṃvattanti?"
msgstr ""
"And how are the seven awakening factors developed and cultivated so as to "
"lead to giving up the things that are prone to being fettered?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.29:2.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ … pe … "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ "
"vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, "
"investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and "
"equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen "
"as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.29:2.2"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā evaṃ bahulīkatā saṃyojanīyānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ pahānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated so as to "
"lead to giving up the things that are prone to being fettered."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.89"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.29:3.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṃyojanīyā dhammā?"
msgstr "And what are the things that are prone to being fettered?"

msgctxt "sn46.29:3.2"
msgid "Cakkhu, bhikkhave, saṃyojanīyo dhammo."
msgstr "The eye is something that’s prone to being fettered."

msgctxt "sn46.29:3.3"
msgid "Etthete uppajjanti saṃyojanavinibandhā ajjhosānā … pe …"
msgstr "This is where these fetters, shackles, and attachments arise."

msgctxt "sn46.29:3.4"
msgid "jivhā saṃyojanīyā dhammā."
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn46.29:3.5"
msgid "Etthete uppajjanti saṃyojanavinibandhā ajjhosānā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.29:3.6"
msgid "mano saṃyojanīyo dhammo."
msgstr "mind is something that’s prone to being fettered."

msgctxt "sn46.29:3.7"
msgid "Etthete uppajjanti saṃyojanavinibandhā ajjhosānā."
msgstr "This is where these fetters, shackles, and attachments arise."

msgctxt "sn46.29:3.8"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṃyojanīyā dhammā”ti."
msgstr "These are called the things that are prone to being fettered.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.29:3.9"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
